}</meta><meta name="external">https://www2.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/~streicher/NOTES/lift.pdf</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15034</anchor> <rss>emmenegger-mesiti-rosolini-streicher-2023.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Reference</taxon> <addr>emmenegger-mesiti-rosolini-streicher-2023</addr>  <route>emmenegger-mesiti-rosolini-streicher-2023.xml</route>  <authors><author><link href="jacopoemmenegger.xml" type="local">Jacopo Emmenegger</link></author><author><link href="lucamesiti.xml" type="local">Luca Mesiti</link></author><author><link href="pinorosolini.xml" type="local">Guiseppe Rosolini</link></author><author><link href="thomasstreicher.xml" type="local">Thomas Streicher</link></author> </authors> <title>A comonad for Grothendieck fibrations</title> <meta name="doi">10.48550/arXiv.2305.01474</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>We study the 2-category theory of Grothendieck fibrations in the 2-category of functors <tex>\mathbf{Cat} ^{ \to }</tex>. After redrawing a few general results in that context, we show that fibrations over a given base are pseudo-coalgebras for a 2-comonad on  <tex>{ \mathbf{Cat} } _{ / B }</tex>. We use that result to explain how an arbitrary fibration is equivalent to one with a splitting.</p></mainmatter> </tree></references></backmatter></tree>